{
  "texts": [
    "Shelke and Vanjale [87] conducted a variety of studies to compare the effects of NER with conventional implanting and rapid text installing layers in order to investigate the presentation of word inserting with varied group sizes and develop deep learning models with the dataset of approx. 2600 sentences.",
    "The precision value of the proposed system design is 76.13%, which is significantly higher than that of earlier architectures.",
    "Additionally, the recall and F1-score values for the suggested system architecture are 71.49 and 74.26, respectively.",
    "Sharma et al. [88] demonstrated a deep neural network architecture on the basis of CRF, CNN and bidirectional long short-term memory (Bi-LSTM) neural network (NN) for named entity identification for the resource-limited language Hindi.",
    "In the suggested method, the authors first encoded the words in semantic vectors that are applied in various deep neural network-based [89] architectures by using the skip-gram word2vec model and GloVe model."
  ]
}